  <h1 id="title">Traffic accidents in Helsinki area</h1>


  <h3>Introduction</h3>

  <p class="text-field">
    We have done research based on the open datasets on <a href="https://www.avoindata.fi/data/fi/dataset/tieliikenneonnettomuudet">Road traffic accidents</a> and <a href="https://www.avoindata.fi/data/fi/dataset/liikennemaarat-helsingissa">Traffic Volumes</a> in the Helsinki area.
    Our initial plan was to find correlations between the traffic volumes and the road accidents on different streets in Helsinki.
    We also wanted to see if the data would reveal are any especially dangerous roads.
    <br>
    Following when we talk about annual ’traffic volume’ on a certain road, we mean the amount motor vehicles that annually pass a certain measurement point.

    <br><br>

    The dataset ‘Traffic Volumes’ in Helsinki provides information on the volumes of different vehicles on the streets of Helsinki from the year 2011 onwards. The traffic volumes were counted hourly (Monday-Thursday) in September and October, so the data represents average daily volumes during these two months.
    <br>
    The other dataset ‘Road traffic accidents’ contains records of all traffic accidents in Finland (except in Åland) from 2005 to 2016. We used the data from 2011 to 2016, and selected the entries that are in Helsinki area.
  </p>


